    stem: "A 30-year-old female with PCOS and anovulatory infertility desires pregnancy. Her provider recommends letrozole as first-line ovulation induction. The patient asks why letrozole is preferred over clomiphene. What is letrozole's mechanism in ovulation induction, and how does it differ from clomiphene's SERM mechanism?",
    optionA: "Letrozole directly stimulates FSH release from the pituitary through a SERM mechanism identical to clomiphene; it is preferred only because it costs less",
